y = 100 * correct / total\nprint(f\"\\nTest Accuracy: {test_accuracy:.2f}%\")\n","metadata":{"id":"CzbO9YeSV0Db","outputId":"8158799e-d5d5-43a9-8f6f-98be6b72efbc","trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-01-25T11:47:35.735349Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-01-25T11:47:35.735670Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-01-25T11:47:42.294828Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-01-25T11:47:35.735647Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-01-25T11:47:42.290270Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\nTest Accuracy: 83.69%\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":55},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"As Expected, ResNet didn't improve our accuracy,","metadata":{"id":"Y_DfFNQcpqCE"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Since we are feeding only 1-channel grayscale input instead of standard 3-channel RGB. Most pretrained networks are optimized for 3-channel input. This reduces the model's learning capacity unless trained longer.","metadata":{"id":"voHcLOFGqivv"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Lets still see the confusion matrix","metadata":{"id":"K_cJWdTprL3M"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\nclass_names = ['Mild Demented', 'Moderate Demented', 'Non Demented', 'Very Mild Demented']\n\n# Confusion Matrix\ncm = confusion_matrix(all_labels, all_preds)\nplt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\nsns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names)\nplt.xlabel('Predicted')\nplt.ylabel('Actual')\nplt.title('Confusion Matrix')\nplt.show()\n\n","metadata":{"id":"kZP2cHS5kbi8","outputId":"7e0dd83d-c612-45a6-8a59-9991b50d473d","trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-01-25T11:48:02.850087Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-01-25T11:48:02.850326Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-01-25T11:48:02.993782Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-01-25T11:48:02.850307Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-01-25T11:48:02.990015Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 600x500 with 2 Axes>","image/png":""},"metadata":{}}],"execu