n## CNN with Data Augmentation:\nModerate results were observed with slight improvement in generalization, but still not surpassing the initial model.\n- an accuracy of 64.22%\n\n## ResNet model From scratch:\nBuilt the Resnet model from scratch. Didn't get good results as expected.\n- an accuracy of 55.7%\n\n## Transfer Learning with Pretrained ResNet18:\nSurprisingly, this approach yielded only 43.12% accuracy. While pretrained models are expected to outperform models trained from scratch, the poor performance here could be attributed to:\n- Input channel mismatch (Grayscale to RGB conversion issues),\n- Improper normalization or resizing,\n- Freezing of too many layers (leading to underfitting),\n- Incompatibility of pretrained features with medical imaging data.\n\n## Key Takeaway:\n- though there is room for improvement, and there may exist possibility to go over 98% , We can say this project is highly succesful since got a very strong 96.95% of accuracy, and had a good hands on different modelling approaches.","metadata":{"id":"TquDoI2oPGlR"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Kindly upvote, if this helped.","metadata":{"id":"LU_DwQ4KShPZ","jp-MarkdownHeadingCollapsed":true}}]}